Subject: [experiment] ESM4 actor root attachment audit

Status: experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Depends-on: 0010-esm4-face-rig-render-buffer-audit.patch,
0011-esm4-actor-controller-basis-audit.patch,
0012-esm4-native-callback-basis-audit.patch.
Proof baseline: run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-225321.

0013 showed that native callback actor-basis modes change limb scatter but do
not make FO3/FNV actors upright. Plain root-up wrapper probes also changed the
failure mode without producing a valid pose. The next diagnostic slice needs a
compact root/world transform row that can be compared against part-matrix and
visual evidence.

This patch preserves behavior. When OPENMW_FNV_ROOT_ATTACHMENT_AUDIT=1 or
OPENMW_ESM4_ROOT_ATTACHMENT_AUDIT=1 is set, it logs the actor root world basis,
major Bip01 target positions, and head/foot/root deltas for the visible runtime
path.

